body:
Decided to seriously start tracking these calories today so I meal prepped this am. I also have tracked my main meals for the day and part of tomorrow, too!

Started off with a slow walk on the treadmill, then realized after 10 minutes that I’d have to walk another 90 minutes to burn 500 calories at that pace. So, I hopped off and did day 3 of Insanity. By the end of the WARM-UP I had already burned almost 200 more calories.

The third pic is just me marveling at how terrible my genes are. Those dark lines are my veins, which are pretty much visible everywhere. Not an attractive quality, but hey, I’ll be an easy stick if I ever need IV access.

blog.name: epic-unicorn
blog.title: It’s Not The Length Of Life

body:
Your Child’s Mental Health

Depression and bipolar-depression is the worst mental health battle I can think of, what’s even more rough is seeing someone struggle with it as well.

My brother is 16 years old and is struggling with major bipolar-depression. He rarely eats, he doesn’t talk, he sleeps all day, and takes hour long showers; all of these things are signs of depression. I notice these things and tell my parents they need to have him talk to a therapist and be on a prescription to help him with how he feels. My parents come from a place of complete denial and refuse to believe he has a mental illiness that needs to be medicated.

My brother has voiced multiple times how he wants to kill himself and my parents express that he doesn’t need to feel that way because he “gets everything he wants in life.”

I am not my brothers guardian, I cannot get him the medical help he needs. I wish my parents would realize the importance of mental health and how it should be taken seriously.

For all you parents out there… mental health is serious, it is not something you sweep under the rug, it will not just go away with time. Let your child get help, let them talk to someone about why they feel the way they feel. Let your children have a chance at life.

summary: I am super thrilled with this 😍 My average weight is down to 270.2, so by the scale I am down 6.8 and by average I am done 4.4....
body:
1.16.19 - Weigh In Wednesday - 268.8 (-6.8)

I am super thrilled with this 😍 My average weight is down to 270.2, so by the scale I am down 6.8 and by average I am done 4.4. Neither of which are too shabby, in my opinion. I wanted to do the side by sides more for myself, I guess. I feel like I see some subtle differences - but I also have my period and feel like a blob so 🤷‍♀️ At the very least I don’t feel bloated the way I do when I eat poorly. Just regular ol’ period bloat 😂

I don’t have much to say. I’m going to continue IF and eating as Keto as possible, and starting next week probably exercise since my ankle is better and better every day.

Hope you all have a great Wednesday!

summary: Chemotherapy + stem cell transplantation has nearly completely halted MS disease progression in a randomized trial. The trial...
caption: Chemotherapy + stem cell transplantation has nearly completely halted MS disease progression in a randomized trial. The trial randomized 110 patients to either stem cell transplant or standard, disease modifying therapy. Only 3 patients on transplant had disease progression vs. 34 on SOC.

reblog.comment: Chemotherapy + stem cell transplantation has nearly completely halted MS disease progression in a randomized trial. The trial randomized 110 patients to either stem cell transplant or standard, disease modifying therapy. Only 3 patients on transplant had disease progression vs. 34 on SOC.
